get_multi_input_switching_mode(25.10)    get_multi_input_switching_mode(25.10)

Name  get_multi_input_switching_mode - Reports the MIS (multi-input switching)
       analysis settings configured using  the  set_multi_input_switching_mode
       command
Syntax
Parameters -help Prints out the command usage. -disable_lib_cells <string> Re-
       ports  all  the  user-specified  library  cells  for  which multi-input
       switching (MIS) mode support is disabled. -mis_alignment_mode {0  |  1}
       Returns  the  current  value  set  (0  or 1) of the MIS alignment mode.
       -switching_alignment_factor <<float>> Returns the  switching  alignment
       factor specified globally.
